# .vexpignore — paths excluded from vexp's code index/ranking (gitignore syntax).
# These files STAY in git; they're just kept out of run_pipeline's ranked context so
# source code isn't crowded out by process/handoff prose. Tune per project.
#
# vexp's built-in excludes already cover: node_modules, .git, dist, .next, target,
# __pycache__, .vexp. The SecurityFilter already drops .env / credentials. Only add
# things that ARE committed source-tree files but make poor ranked context.

# Completed/failed handoff prompts — historical, never useful as live code context.
prompts/done/
prompts/failed/

# Other common candidates (uncomment per project):
# standards.md
# CHANGELOG.md
# docs/**/*.md        # only if spec/decision docs are crowding out code in results
